"People are very overstretched, housing is expensive, as is education, and because of this a lot of people put it off," says the young manager.
Other people may have children.
"But it's important for me to have my own money and time," says another young man, 20.
Men and women cite their careers, stress and house prices and education as reasons that prevent them from having children.
So, no matter how hard the Government tries to encourage its citizens to have children, in terms of procreation, Singaporeans have the final say.
