I remember winning for the first time against the United States during the Olympic qualifying tournament in Mexico in 1989.
Then came the 1990 World Cup, where we got fourth place and it was going to be bronze, were it not for the Canadian referee who made us replay the final game," Reyes said.
That team from the 1990 World Cup is the best team you've ever seen?
She is among the best, as well as the one that won against Dream Team at the 2004 Olympics.
But my favorite was that from the Pan American Games in Cuba in 1991, when we won gold and defeated the U.S. team, which was quite similar to the one that won us bronze at the World Championships.
Not only did Mincy, Gauss, Ramon Rivas, Fico Lopez and Piculina (Ortiz) play again, but also the young (Javier) 'Tonito' Colon and James Carter, brothers Leon (Francisco and Edgar) and Mario 'Kihote' Morales, who was unable to participate in 90 due to a knee injury.
The team, which may not have been the best in terms of personnel, but brought us a gold medal and great joy, was the team of the 1995 Olympic qualifying tournament in Neuquen, Argentina.
